Definition: experiencing or marked by or expressing sorrow especially that associated with irreparable loss
Example: sorrowful widows; a sorrowful tale of death and despair; sorrowful news; even in laughter the heart is sorrowful- Proverbs 14:13
Synonyms: noun, state, sorrowfulness, feeling, JOYFUL, JOYLESS, UNHAPPY, experiencing, or, marked, by, expressing, sorrow, especially, that, associated, with, irreparable, loss, sorrowful, widows, a, tale, of, death, and, despair, news, even, in, laughter, the, heart, is, -, Proverbs
Category: adj.all
